Bluetongue, Hungary
-------------------
Information received on 15 Oct 2014 from Dr Lajos Bogar, Deputy State Secretary Chief Veterinary Officer, Food Chain Safety Department, Ministry of Agriculture, Budapest, Hungary

Summary:
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 14 Oct 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 14 Oct 2014
Report date: 14 Oct 2014
Date submitted to OIE: 15 Oct 2014
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 10 Dec 2008
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 4
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1: Hodmezovasarhely, Csongrad
Date of start of the outbreak: 14 Oct 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 2 / 1 / 0 / 1 / 0

Outbreak 2: Deszk, Csongrad
Date of start of the outbreak: 14 Oct 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 12 / 4 / 0 / 4 / 0

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 14 / 4 / 0 / 4 / 0

Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 28.57 percent / 0 percent / 0 percent / 28.57 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: vectors

Control measures
Measures applied: control of arthropods; movement control inside the country; screening; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); modified stamping out; vaccination prohibited; no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Veterinary Diagnostic Directorate of National Food Chain Safety Office (National Reference Laboratory) (National laboratory) / Cattle / antibody detection ELISA / 14 Oct 2014 / Positive
Veterinary Diagnostic Directorate of National Food Chain Safety Office (National Reference Laboratory) (National laboratory) / Cattle / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (RT-PCR) / 14 Oct 2014 / Positive

Future Reporting:
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of these outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

